---
description: Boundaries between Unity input callbacks and application/use case flow
globs: Assets/Game/Presentation/**/*.cs, Assets/Game/Application/**/*.cs
alwaysApply: false
---

# Input Boundary

- Read Unity Input System, pointer, click, keyboard, touch, and gesture callbacks only inside Presentation adapters.
- Collect Photon Fusion input inside Presentation/network adapters; Fusion input structs should carry gameplay intent and stable IDs, not scene references or service objects.
- Do not mutate gameplay state inside input callbacks; forward input intent to a presenter/controller/use case through an explicit method or event.
- Keep input action names, bindings, and device choices on the authoring/config side; `Application` must not know input devices or Unity callbacks.
- Interpret UI gestures such as debounce, double-click, hold, and drag threshold in Presentation; gameplay validity stays in UseCase/Application.
- Input subscription lifecycle must be explicit; guarantee unsubscribe through `OnEnable`/`OnDisable` or owner cancellation.
- Do not pass IDs, indexes, or pointer targets from input to a use case without validation; use stable domain IDs.

## Example

```csharp
// BAD: Button callback mutates state directly
public void OnUpgradeClicked()
{
    _state.Money -= 100;
}

// GOOD: Input intent moves into presenter/use case flow
public void OnUpgradeClicked()
{
    _presenter.RequestBuyUpgrade(_upgradeId);
}
```
